#: ../../F/for-free.rst:5
msgid "for free"
msgstr "for free"

#: ../../F/for-free.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../F/for-free.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] Said of a capability of a programming language or hardware that is "
"available by its design without needing cleverness to implement: \"In APL, "
"we get the matrix operations for free.\" \"And owing to the way revisions "
"are stored in this system, you get revision trees for free.\" The term "
"usually refers to a serendipitous feature of doing things a certain way "
"(compare :ref:`big-win`\\), but it may refer to an intentional but secondary"
" feature."
msgstr ""
"[一般的]プログラミング言語やハードウェアの、その設計によって、巧妙な実装の工夫を要さずに利用できる能力について言う。「APLでは、行列演算がfor "
"free(ただ)で手に入る」「そしてこのシステムでのリビジョンの保存のされ方のおかげで、リビジョンツリーがfor "
"freeで手に入る」。この用語はたいてい、あるやり方で物事を行うことの思いがけない特徴を指す(\\ :ref:`big-win`\\ "
"と比較せよ)が、意図的だが副次的な特徴を指すこともある。"
